body:
Hi there, my first time asking a question here :)

I don't have any problems at the moment (loving the react hooks btw).

I just want to ask for ideas on how to handle a particular scenario i have and if i am using the context hooks properly.

So my situation is with a form like this:

Context file: 

```
export const StepsContext = createContext({
    steps: []
});

```

This would be the "parent" component. 
```
const steps = useContext(StepsContext);

const sendForm = () => {
  callEndpoint(steps);
};

return <Form>

  <Input />  // Default input always present
  <Steps /> // Component that dynamically adds more inputs as i click on a button.

  <button onClck={sendForm} />
</Form>  
```

Inside the Steps component
```
// This component adds more inputs as i click on a button and sets a "config" state with the 
// values of each input, in an array that looks kinda like [ 0: { value: "value" }  ]
// Each new index is a new input

const context = useContext(StepsContext);
const [inputs, setInputs] = useState([]);

return <button onClick={addNewInput}/>

const addNewInput = () => {
 // Do something to add new input and set the config, so if we have two the config looks like:
// [ 0: { value: "somethig"}, 1: { value: "else" } ]

// And now i update the context so the parent knows how many steps we have and their config
context.steps = newConfig;
}
```

This works and i get the data where i want it, but for some reason this assignment i do: `context.steps = newConfig;` feels wrong hehe.

Am i doing it right? 
Can anyone throw any ideas at me on how to approach this or do it in a nicer way?

Thanks and kind regards.
